From Gordon Banks Subject Re Sleeping Pill OD In article A daniel federman writes A friend of mine took appoximately CVS sleeping pills, each containing mg of diphenhydramine, I think That's mg, total I'm worried, though, about the long term effects Since he never had his stomach pumped, will he have liver or brain damage Any information would be greatly appreciated Shouldn't have But he may need to see the shrink about why he wanted to kill himself Depressed people can be succesfully treated usually Gordon Banks N JXP Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect, and it is shameful to surrender it too soon